{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17627209","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17627209"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:46:04+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:46:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17107"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17107","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17107"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.8,0.13,0.03,0.01,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9797"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76996"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9797"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17107"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62502"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"171"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22975"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23071"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76996","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76996"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDual antiplatelet therapy with aspirin and clopidogrel is commonly prescribed after acute coronary syndromes and coronary stent placement to prevent thrombosis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of action when aspirin and clopidogrel are used in combination?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inhibition of separate platelet activation pathways","Inhibition of cyclooxygenase enzymes by both drugs","Elevation of cyclic adenosine monophosphate by both drugs","Blockade of adenosine diphosphate receptors by both drugs","Prevention of calcium release by both drugs"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibition of separate platelet activation pathways\u003C/strong\u003E. Aspirin irreversibly inhibits cyclooxygenase-1, preventing the formation of thromboxane A2, while clopidogrel blocks the P2Y12 adenosine diphosphate receptor. This combination provides more complete platelet inhibition than either agent alone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibition of cyclooxygenase enzymes by both drugs\u003C/strong\u003E: Only aspirin acts through cyclooxygenase inhibition, while clopidogrel works via a different mechanism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElevation of cyclic adenosine monophosphate by both drugs\u003C/strong\u003E: Neither drug primarily works by increasing cyclic adenosine monophosphate levels in platelets.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlockade of adenosine diphosphate receptors by both drugs\u003C/strong\u003E: Only clopidogrel acts by blocking P2Y12 adenosine diphosphate receptors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevention of calcium release by both drugs\u003C/strong\u003E: While both medications ultimately reduce platelet activation, neither directly interferes with calcium release as their primary mechanism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe complementary mechanisms of action explain why dual antiplatelet therapy is more effective than monotherapy in preventing thrombotic events after coronary interventions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Aspirin irreversibly inhibits cyclooxygenase-1 to prevent thromboxane A2 production and platelet aggregation.","P2Y12 inhibitors like clopidogrel block ADP-mediated platelet activation.","Dual antiplatelet therapy combines two different mechanisms of platelet inhibition for more effective prevention of thrombosis."],"references":["Virk HUH, Escobar J, Rodriguez M, Bates ER, Khalid U, Jneid H, Birnbaum Y, Levine GN, Smith SC Jr, Krittanawong C. Dual Antiplatelet Therapy: A Concise Review for Clinicians. Life (Basel). 2023 Jul 18;13(7):1580. doi: 10.3390/life13071580. PMID: 37511955; PMCID: PMC10381391.","Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62502"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17107"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62502","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62502"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T22:07:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T22:09:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9797"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76996"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":